cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about aspect-level sentiment classification (ASC) using neural models with attention mechanisms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also proposes a self-supervised learning approach, which involves training models without human supervision, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of regularization to improve attention mechanisms suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible category. The paper also involves mining useful information from a training corpus, which falls under the scope of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of neural models suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category.
